Here is a handy cheat sheet of the most common Docker commands you will need for this specific project (Udemy Course Finder), based on your `docker-compose.yml` configuration:

### 🚀 Starting & Stopping the Project

**Start all services in the background** (Builds the images if they don't exist yet):
```bash
docker compose up -d
```

**Force rebuild and start all services** (Use this after making changes to `Dockerfile`s or installing new npm packages):
```bash
docker compose up --build -d
```

**Stop all running services**:
```bash
docker compose down
```

**Stop services AND wipe the database/cache** (Removes containers and volumes. Use this for a complete hard reset of your Postgres and Redis data):
```bash
docker compose down -v
```

