docker system prune -a --volumes -f


If you want a single "Nuke Everything" command that you can copy and paste to completely obliterate all stopped containers, unused networks, all cached layers, all images, and wipe the Docker Desktop UI build history in one go, here it is:

```bash
docker system prune -a --volumes -f && docker builder prune -a -f && docker buildx history rm --all
```

**What this chained command does in order:**
1. `docker system prune -a --volumes -f`: Deletes all stopped containers, unused networks, all images (not just dangling ones), and all unused volumes.
2. `docker builder prune -a -f`: Massively clears out the hidden BuildKit cache (this fixes the "no space left on device" errors).
3. `docker buildx history rm --all`: Clears the visual build history list shown in the Docker Desktop UI.

You can save this somewhere handy and run it anytime Docker feels bloated or buggy!
